{
  "video_id": "yBdyFKqwKy0",
  "title": "How we'll find life on other planets | Aomawa Shields",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12856.0,
      "end_time": 17595.0,
      "text": "I am in search of another planet in the universe where life exists."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 18426.0,
      "end_time": 21387.0,
      "text": "I can&#39;t see this planet with my naked eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21412.0,
      "end_time": 23698.0,
      "text": "or even with the most powerful telescopes"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23722.0,
      "end_time": 25720.0,
      "text": "we currently possess."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25787.0,
      "end_time": 27851.0,
      "text": "But I know that it&#39;s there."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27875.0,
      "end_time": 31180.0,
      "text": "And understanding contradictions that occur in nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31420.0,
      "end_time": 32398.0,
      "text": "will help us find it."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33379.0,
      "end_time": 34530.0,
      "text": "On our planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34554.0,
      "end_time": 36527.0,
      "text": "where there&#39;s water, there&#39;s life."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36892.0,
      "end_time": 39826.0,
      "text": "So we look for planets that orbit at just the right distance"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39850.0,
      "end_time": 41149.0,
      "text": "from their stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42418.0,
      "end_time": 43569.0,
      "text": "At this distance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 43593.0,
      "end_time": 47730.0,
      "text": "shown in blue on this diagram for stars of different temperatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47970.0,
      "end_time": 50951.0,
      "text": "planets could be warm enough for water to flow on their surfaces"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50975.0,
      "end_time": 52373.0,
      "text": "as lakes and oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52397.0,
      "end_time": 53937.0,
      "text": "where life might reside."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 54787.0,
      "end_time": 58501.0,
      "text": "Some astronomers focus their time and energy on finding planets"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58525.0,
      "end_time": 60966.0,
      "text": "at these distances from their stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 60990.0,
      "end_time": 63393.0,
      "text": "What I do picks up where their job ends."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 63869.0,
      "end_time": 66853.0,
      "text": "I model the possible climates of exoplanets."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 67353.0,
      "end_time": 69178.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s why that&#39;s important:"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 69203.0,
      "end_time": 72693.0,
      "text": "there are many factors besides distance from its star"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 72717.0,
      "end_time": 75321.0,
      "text": "that control whether a planet can support life."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 76297.0,
      "end_time": 77813.0,
      "text": "Take the planet Venus."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 78646.0,
      "end_time": 82337.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s named after the Roman goddess of love and beauty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 82361.0,
      "end_time": 85971.0,
      "text": "because of its benign, ethereal appearance in the sky."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86487.0,
      "end_time": 89651.0,
      "text": "But spacecraft measurements revealed a different story."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90800.0,
      "end_time": 94480.0,
      "text": "The surface temperature is close to 900 degrees Fahrenheit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 94730.0,
      "end_time": 95571.0,
      "text": "500 Celsius."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96151.0,
      "end_time": 98539.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s hot enough to melt lead."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99115.0,
      "end_time": 102952.0,
      "text": "Its thick atmosphere, not its distance from the sun, is the reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 102977.0,
      "end_time": 106800.0,
      "text": "It causes a greenhouse effect on steroids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106104.0,
      "end_time": 109744.0,
      "text": "trapping heat from the sun and scorching the planet&#39;s surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110181.0,
      "end_time": 114728.0,
      "text": "The reality totally contradicted initial perceptions of this planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 115728.0,
      "end_time": 118348.0,
      "text": "From these lessons from our own solar system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 118373.0,
      "end_time": 120389.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve learned that a planet&#39;s atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 120413.0,
      "end_time": 124150.0,
      "text": "is crucial to its climate and potential to host life."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124967.0,
      "end_time": 127882.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t know what the atmospheres of these planets are like"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127906.0,
      "end_time": 132274.0,
      "text": "because the planets are so small and dim compared to their stars"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 132298.0,
      "end_time": 133963.0,
      "text": "and so far away from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 134500.0,
      "end_time": 138791.0,
      "text": "For example, one of the closest planets that could support surface water --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 138815.0,
      "end_time": 142172.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s called Gliese 667 Cc --"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 142196.0,
      "end_time": 146132.0,
      "text": "such a glamorous name, right, nice phone number for a name --"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 146156.0,
      "end_time": 148591.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s 23 light years away."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 149910.0,
      "end_time": 151861.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s more than 100 trillion miles."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 152686.0,
      "end_time": 154999.0,
      "text": "Trying to measure the atmospheric composition"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 155230.0,
      "end_time": 159390.0,
      "text": "of an exoplanet passing in front of its host star is hard."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 159444.0,
      "end_time": 161323.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s like trying to see a fruit fly"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 161348.0,
      "end_time": 163634.0,
      "text": "passing in front of a car&#39;s headlight."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 164126.0,
      "end_time": 167825.0,
      "text": "OK, now imagine that car is 100 trillion miles away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 167849.0,
      "end_time": 171221.0,
      "text": "and you want to know the precise color of that fly."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 172618.0,
      "end_time": 174375.0,
      "text": "So I use computer models"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 174399.0,
      "end_time": 177502.0,
      "text": "to calculate the kind of atmosphere a planet would need"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 177526.0,
      "end_time": 180225.0,
      "text": "to have a suitable climate for water and life."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 181439.0,
      "end_time": 185551.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an artist&#39;s concept of the planet Kepler-62f,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 185575.0,
      "end_time": 187580.0,
      "text": "with the Earth for reference."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 187507.0,
      "end_time": 189547.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s 1,200 light years away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189571.0,
      "end_time": 191798.0,
      "text": "and just 40 percent larger than Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 192313.0,
      "end_time": 196361.0,
      "text": "Our NSF-funded work found that it could be warm enough for open water"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 196385.0,
      "end_time": 200494.0,
      "text": "from many types of atmospheres and orientations of its orbit."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 200518.0,
      "end_time": 203651.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;d like future telescopes to follow up on this planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 203675.0,
      "end_time": 205246.0,
      "text": "to look for signs of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 206476.0,
      "end_time": 209865.0,
      "text": "Ice on a planet&#39;s surface is also important for climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 209889.0,
      "end_time": 213840.0,
      "text": "Ice absorbs longer, redder wavelengths of light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 213108.0,
      "end_time": 215238.0,
      "text": "and reflects shorter, bluer light."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 215870.0,
      "end_time": 218759.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why the iceberg in this photo looks so blue."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 219920.0,
      "end_time": 222589.0,
      "text": "The redder light from the sun is absorbed on its way through the ice."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 222613.0,
      "end_time": 225470.0,
      "text": "Only the blue light makes it all the way to the bottom."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 225947.0,
      "end_time": 228339.0,
      "text": "Then it gets reflected back to up to our eyes"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 228363.0,
      "end_time": 229939.0,
      "text": "and we see blue ice."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 230590.0,
      "end_time": 233564.0,
      "text": "My models show that planets orbiting cooler stars"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 233588.0,
      "end_time": 236756.0,
      "text": "could actually be warmer than planets orbiting hotter stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 236780.0,
      "end_time": 238319.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s another contradiction --"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 238343.0,
      "end_time": 242117.0,
      "text": "that ice absorbs the longer wavelength light from cooler stars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 242141.0,
      "end_time": 245249.0,
      "text": "and that light, that energy, heats the ice."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 246622.0,
      "end_time": 248982.0,
      "text": "Using climate models to explore"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 249600.0,
      "end_time": 252111.0,
      "text": "how these contradictions can affect planetary climate"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 252135.0,
      "end_time": 255309.0,
      "text": "is vital to the search for life elsewhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 256128.0,
      "end_time": 259305.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s no surprise that this is my specialty."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 259714.0,
      "end_time": 262500.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m an African-American female astronomer"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 262524.0,
      "end_time": 264636.0,
      "text": "and a classically trained actor"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 264660.0,
      "end_time": 268495.0,
      "text": "who loves to wear makeup and read fashion magazines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 268519.0,
      "end_time": 273352.0,
      "text": "so I am uniquely positioned to appreciate contradictions in nature --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 273376.0,
      "end_time": 274488.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 274512.0,
      "end_time": 277976.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 278000.0,
      "end_time": 282930.0,
      "text": "... and how they can inform our search for the next planet where life exists."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 282645.0,
      "end_time": 285152.0,
      "text": "My organization, Rising Stargirls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 285177.0,
      "end_time": 288605.0,
      "text": "teaches astronomy to middle-school girls of color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 288629.0,
      "end_time": 292850.0,
      "text": "using theater, writing and visual art."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 292697.0,
      "end_time": 296674.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s another contradiction -- science and art don&#39;t often go together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 296698.0,
      "end_time": 300500.0,
      "text": "but interweaving them can help these girls bring their whole selves"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 300524.0,
      "end_time": 301723.0,
      "text": "to what they learn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 301747.0,
      "end_time": 305187.0,
      "text": "and maybe one day join the ranks of astronomers"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 305211.0,
      "end_time": 306965.0,
      "text": "who are full of contradictions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 306989.0,
      "end_time": 310138.0,
      "text": "and use their backgrounds to discover, once and for all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 310163.0,
      "end_time": 313179.0,
      "text": "that we are truly not alone in the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 314433.0,
      "end_time": 315584.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 315608.0,
      "end_time": 324424.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}